author: Rachel Olding, Megan Levy
title: Firefighters battle massive factory fire in Chullora
text:
Firefighters battle massive factory fire in Chullora Rachel Olding, Megan Levy twitter TWEET More 
Firefighters are battling a huge blaze at a waste recycling centre at Chullora that has sent a plume of thick black smoke across Sydney's skyline. 
The fire broke out at centre on Muir Street, Chullora, just before 9.30am. SHARE Black smoke is seen billowing from the factory fire in Chullora. Photo: Seven News on Periscope 
"We've got a large factory fire, that's all I can say at the moment," Fire and Rescue NSW Superintendent Ian Krimmer said. 
All people at the site had been accounted for, Fire and Rescue NSW said. SHARE Smoke from the Chullora factory fire in western Sydney, as seen from Camperdown. Photo: Supplied 
A number of factories surrounding the waste recycling centre were evacuated due to fears that the intense fire could spread. 
At 10am, 11 fire trucks were already on the scene and 15 more were on their way. Advertisement 
Firefighters were attacking the blaze from both sides of the waste recycling centre. 
A NSW Ambulance spokesman said paramedics were on standby on Muir Street. They had not treated any patients.
